h3. Summary
The returned message for a PUT request to update the Epic Link custom field is not accurate. The request completes successfully but the message {{204 No Content}} is returned.

h3. Environment
Tested in JIRA 6.3.10 using [Postman REST Client|https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/postman-rest-client-packa/fhbjgbiflinjbdggehcddcbncdddomop?hl=en] and cURL

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Use Postman REST Client, send a [PUT request|https://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/6.3.10/#d2e1105] to update Epic Link custom field
# Use the following JSON data
{code}
{
    "fields": {
       "customfield_10006": "SSP-24"
       }
}
{code}
(i) 10006 refers to the customfieldId for Epic Link; and SSP-24 is an Epic

h3. Expected Results
Response code 200 (success)

h3. Actual Results
{{204 No Content}} with "Malformed JSON" message

!postman.png|thumbnail!

